### Addtional Distrubution Options
### Addtional Columns
With additional columns we can essencailly make a mini P6 that could be used to produce look ahead schedules what if scenarios where you can change the distribution of resources.

With relationship data, critical path could be calculated, and highlighted.

All the user would need to provide is a SINGLE start date and durations for each activity, and the relationship columns, probably set default to "FS with next".

```
Pseudo Code:
Inside AssignDistributionToDates loop:

currentFinishDateColumn = cell(current row, finishDateCol#)
If currentFinishDateColumn == "":
    Take the last currentDate in that loop and assign the finishDate to that date

# If the start column for the next activity is empty. If there is no duration, then there will be a msg box pop up with a warning

#take activity ID return finishDate or startDate:
def IDDate(relationship):
    id = relationship
    row = index(id, activityIDs)
    startDate = cellValue(row, startDateColumn)
    finishDate = cellValue(row, finishDateColumn)
    dates = [startDate, finishDate]
    return dates


Lag = 0 #Default
relationship = cellValue #at relationship Column
previousFinishDate = currentRow-1, column = finishDate
previousStartDate = currentRow-1, column = startDate 

If startDateColumn == "":
    Look at the relationship column
    If relationshipType == FS:
        If relationship is "Next":
            If lagValue NOT "":
                lag = lagValue
            startDate = previousFinishDate + Lag
        Else:
            IdFinishDate = IDDate(relationship)[1]
            startDate = IdFinishDate + Lag

    If relationshipType == SS:
        If relationship is "Next":
            If lagValue NOT "":
                lag = lagValue
            startDate = previousStartDate + Lag
        Else:
            IdStartDate = IDDate(relationship)[0]
            startDate = IdStartDate + Lag
Continue to next line...
```

